5.full form of WSGI?
The Web Server Gateway Interface (WSGI, pronounced whiskey or WIZ-ghee)
is a simple calling convention for web servers to forward requests to web applications or
frameworks written in the Python programming language. The current version of WSGI,
version 1.0.
